      • getVehicleCountByMinuteDivisionForDirection

        public Map<String,?> getVehicleCountByMinuteDivisionForDirection(Direction direction,
                                                                 int timeInterval,
                                                                 boolean isAverageByDays)
                                                          throws InValidTimeIntervalException
        This method returns vehicle statistics based on time intervals by minutes.
        Parameters:
        direction - The Direction of Vehicles
        timeInterval - A valid time interval. Example 20,30 or 40 minutes required to group by interval per hour.
        isAverageByDays - Is the Report Averaged by total number of Days. If false Then The report Displays Statistics for each Day.
        Returns:
        Map<String,Map<String,Long>> or Map<String,Long> depending upon isAverageByDays flag
        Throws:
        InValidTimeIntervalException - This exception is thrown for invalid intervals. Example intervals <=0
